{"id": 243272260, "title": "Your personal finance questions \u2013 Do I need private health insurance now that public hospital treatment is fre", "text": "Q I have no interest in private hospital cover and always had good experiences with the public system. My VHI Public Plus Care scheme is due for renewal shortly. I am wondering what is the benefit with this plan in light of the fact that treatment for every citizen of Ireland is free in a public hospital? A This is a basic plan from VHI designed to cover public hospitals only, said Dermot Goode of TotalHealthCover.ie, a broker. As in-patient treatment in public hospitals is now free, and given that it\u2019s becoming more difficult to access treatment privately in public hospitals, you are correct to question the value-for-money return on this type of plan.", "summary": "<p><b>Q I have no interest in private hospital cover and always had good experiences with the public system. My VHI Public Plus Care scheme is due for renewal shortly. I am wondering what is the benefit with this plan in light of the fact that treatment for every citizen of Ireland is free in a public hospital?</b></p>", "url": "https://www.independent.ie/business/personal-finance/your-personal-finance-questions-do-i-need-private-health-insurance-now-that-public-hospital-treatment-is-free/a1446650779.html", "image": "https://focus.independent.ie/thumbor/2wY6CXLz6R-PvDCnX-piF4rHcXQ=/0x0:3237x2158/550x550/prod-mh-ireland/7734e150-f7b7-43a8-84c9-8688d243822a/4c00f1e5-c0d1-463d-ae19-b3004140af93/IB%20health%20insurance.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-29 01:30:00", "author": "Charlie Weston", "authors": ["Charlie Weston"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ie", "sentiment": -0.496}